      <div class="clearfix grpelem" id="u7177-6">
       <!-- content -->
       <p>
        <a class="nonblock" href="assets/governance-structure-(website-version).pdf">
         Shared governance
        </a>
        at Virginia Tech is the set of practices under which the university’s governing board, administration, faculty, staff, and students participate in the significant decisions concerning the operation of their institution.  The interdependence among constituent groups at all levels requires complex coordination, excellent communication throughout, and appropriate joint planning and execution.  Why participate in shared governance?  To have a voice in shaping your university.
       </p>
      </div>
     </div>
